## Analyzing flow logs

Flow logs tell us about bytes of data that were sent successfully from the IP address A to B using a protocol on port, with the number of packets transferred and whether the traffic was allowed ("ACCEPT") or rejected ('REJECT")

For example, the flow log I've captured tells us 344 bytes of data were sent successfully from the IP address 18.206.107.28 to 10.1.0.60 using TCP protocol on port 22, with 4 packets transferred, and the traffic was allowed ("ACCEPT").

![Image](http://nextwork.ai/soothed_gold_swift_blueberry/uploads/aws-networks-monitoring_d116818e)

